   138‚Üí### mitt
   139‚Üí
   140‚ÜíMitt: Tiny (~200b) functional event emitter / pubsub.
   141‚Üí
   142‚ÜíReturns **Mitt** 
   143‚Üí
   144‚Üí### all
   145‚Üí
   146‚ÜíA Map of event names to registered handler functions.
   147‚Üí
   148‚Üí### on
   149‚Üí
   150‚ÜíRegister an event handler for the given type.
   151‚Üí
   152‚Üí#### Parameters
   153‚Üí
   154‚Üí-   `type` **([string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String) \| [symbol](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Symbol))** Type of event to listen for, or `'*'` for all events
   155‚Üí-   `handler` **[Function](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/function)** Function to call in response to given event
   156‚Üí
   157‚Üí### off
   158‚Üí
   159‚ÜíRemove an event handler for the given type.
   160‚ÜíIf `handler` is omitted, all handlers of the given type are removed.
   161‚Üí
   162‚Üí#### Parameters
   163‚Üí
   164‚Üí-   `type` **([string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String) \| [symbol](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Symbol))** Type of event to unregister `handler` from, or `'*'`
   165‚Üí-   `handler` **[Function](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/function)?** Handler function to remove
   166‚Üí
   167‚Üí### emit
   168‚Üí
   169‚ÜíInvoke all handlers for the given type.
   170‚ÜíIf present, `'*'` handlers are invoked after type-matched handlers.
   171‚Üí
   172‚ÜíNote: Manually firing '\*' handlers is not supported.
   173‚Üí
   174‚Üí#### Parameters
   175‚Üí
   176‚Üí-   `type` **([string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String) \| [symbol](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Symbol))** The event type to invoke
   177‚Üí-   `evt` **Any?** Any value (object is recommended and powerful), passed to each handler
   178‚Üí
   179‚Üí## Contribute
   180‚Üí
   181‚ÜíFirst off, thanks for taking the time to contribute!
   182‚ÜíNow, take a moment to be sure your contributions make sense to everyone else.
   183‚Üí
   184‚Üí### Reporting Issues
   185‚Üí
   186‚ÜíFound a problem? Want a new feature? First of all see if your issue or idea has [already been reported](../../issues).
   187‚ÜíIf don't, just open a [new clear and descriptive issue](../../issues/new).
   188‚Üí
   189‚Üí### Submitting pull requests
   190‚Üí
   191‚ÜíPull requests are the greatest contributions, so be sure they are focused in scope, and do avoid unrelated commits.
   192‚Üí
   193‚Üí-   Fork it!
   194‚Üí-   Clone your fork: `git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/mitt`
   195‚Üí-   Navigate to the newly cloned directory: `cd mitt`
   196‚Üí-   Create a new branch for the new feature: `git checkout -b my-new-feature`
   197‚Üí-   Install the tools necessary for development: `npm install`
   198‚Üí-   Make your changes.
   199‚Üí-   Commit your changes: `git commit -am 'Add some feature'`
   200‚Üí-   Push to the branch: `git push origin my-new-feature`
   201‚Üí-   Submit a pull request with full remarks documenting your changes.
   202‚Üí
